  "prompt": "What are the 3 best things you would recommend to improve your questions on Quora?",
  "response": "Improving your questions on Quora can lead to better answers and a more engaging discussion. Here are three recommendations:\n\n1. **Be Specific and Clear**: Formulate your question to be as clear and specific as possible. Instead of asking broad questions, try to narrow down the focus. For example, instead of asking, \"What should I know about healthy eating?\" you could ask, \"What are some effective strategies for incorporating more whole foods into my diet?\"\n\n2. **Provide Context**: Offering context helps potential respondents understand your question better and yield more relevant answers. Share any relevant background information, such as your interests, current knowledge level, or specific challenges you're facing. This helps others tailor their responses to your situation.\n\n3. **Engage and Encourage Interaction**: Pose open-ended questions that invite discussion rather than simple yes/no answers. Adding prompts like, \"I'm interested in hearing about personal experiences,\" or \"What are different perspectives on this topic?\" can elicit richer, more varied responses.\n\nBy implementing these suggestions, you can enhance the quality and depth of the answers you receive on Quora.",
